      <section eId="sec_7006">
        <num>7006</num>
        <heading>Removal of directors</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_7006__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>In the case of a corporation having cumulative voting, no director\nmay be removed when the votes cast against his removal would be\nsufficient to elect him if voted cumulatively at an election at which\nthe same total number of votes were cast and the entire board, or the\nentire class of directors of which he is a member, were then being\nelected; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_7006__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>When by the provisions of the organization certificate the holders\nof the shares of any class or series, voting as a class, are entitled to\nelect one or more directors, any director so elected may be removed only\nby the applicable vote of the holders of the shares of that class or\nseries, voting as a class.\n  4. This section does not affect the powers of the superintendent under\nsection forty-one of this chapter.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
